def: One who holds a prior to purchase certain public land. Abbott.
Depurated; cleansed; freed from impurities. Boyle.
Drooling; defiling with saliva.-- Slav"er*ing*ly, adv.
Having no communion or intercourse with each other. [Obs.] SirM. Hale.
Measured by sixty degrees; fixed or indicated by a distance ofsixty degrees. Glanvill.
The act of immortalizing, or state of being immortalized.
A chemical earth, the oxide of scandium.
